\begin_layout Standard
From Table 1 we see that the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\text{\textbf{GARCH}}\left(1,1\right)}$
\end_inset

 model has the lowest 
\begin_inset Formula $BIC$
\end_inset

 for each of the series, thus we would consider 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\text{\textbf{GARCH}}\left(1,1\right)}$
\end_inset

 to be best fitting for the data, and thus the most appropriate model for
 the series.
 From this we can infer that the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\text{\textbf{GARCH}}\left(1,1\right)}$
\end_inset

 is better in terms of its ability to capture the patterns and trends in
 the volatility of the returns.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The BIC is calculated as the negative log-likelihood of the model, plus
 a penalty term that increases with the number of parameters in the model,
 so it may be the case that the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\text{\textbf{GARCH}}\left(1,1\right)}$
\end_inset

 model provides a good balance between fit and complexity, making it the
 most suitable model for these time series, since the BIC are close for
 each series.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If the purpose of research is to look at asymmetries in the volatility,
 it would be appropriate to still consider the 
\series bold

\begin_inset Formula $\text{NAGARCH}$
\end_inset

 
\series default
model.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
e) Consider the series of JP Morgan Chase & Co.
 (ticker JPM).
 Compute 
\begin_inset Formula $E[σ2_{T}+h|F_{T}]\text{ for }h=1,...,50$
\end_inset

 according to the NAGARCH and GARCH models, where 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 is the length of the estimation period.
 Compare the predictions of NAGARCH and GARCH in a picture.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename /Users/tobiasbrammer/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/Documents/Aarhus Uni/7. semester/FinancialEconometrics/Exam2022/img/dji30ret_JPM_forecast.pdf
	lyxscale 50
